.next/
out/
node_modules/
.env
.env.local
*.tsbuildinfo

# ios/ was ignored back when it was a throwaway Capacitor scaffold you could
# recreate with `npx cap add ios`. It isn't that anymore: App/Native/ is a
# hand-written SwiftUI app (44 files, holds @main) and IS the shipped iOS
# product, plus 119 pre-rendered ATC mp3s that cost ElevenLabs credits to
# regenerate. Keeping it ignored meant the real app lived on exactly one
# Mac's disk. Now tracked; only genuinely-derived/per-user junk is excluded.
ios/**/xcuserdata/
ios/**/DerivedData/
ios/**/build/
ios/**/*.xcarchive
ios/**/*.ipa
ios/App/Pods/
ios/App/App/public/

android/
.env.tmp
